	(text "The CSN (Chip Select Not) pin is also Active-Low.\nThis holds the pin High (SPI OFF) forcing the\ndrivers to keep their ears plugged until the\nESP32 explicitly pulls the CS line low to send\na real configuration packet."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 77.978 81.788 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify right top)
		)
		(uuid "0399dd46-bb2e-4903-ba4d-48d0c7d78817")
	)
	(text "Local energy reservoir and Back-EMF snubber.\nStabilizes VMOT during high-current steps and protects\nTMC5160 from voltage spikes during motor deceleration."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 189.738 139.446 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "36647ca0-bfe3-44d5-8b1b-0bde11d9fd15")
	)
	(text "The EN (Enable) pin on the TMC5160 is Active-Low.\nThis holds the pin High (Motors OFF) while the ESP32\nwakes up. Once the ESP32 is ready to move, it easily\noverpowers the resistor and pulls the line Low."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 210.82 81.28 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "a0dfa204-26e2-454c-b324-570b17a6dc8b")
	)
